reviewText: The people could not have been more French.  They looked French even without talking; I loved it and will watch it again and again,  Herb

A simple yet beautiful voyeuristic glimpse into 1970's Paris neighborhood of famed director Agnes Varda (The Beaches of Agnes / Cleo from 5 to 7 / The Gleaners and I / Vagabond). Truly intriguing and engaging.
I had seen the movie a couple of times before buying the DVD, and was so pleased by the bonus features:  Including several insider shorts on making and music and best of all a 21 minute return visit to the Rue Daguerre in 2005.
This film is simply fascinating!!!! Agnes Varda is Genius!!! I had to own it . Who would of thought that a film shot in Paris during the 1970's featuring shopkeepers would be so darn amazing?
